SIMPLE: nest_egg
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: nest egg
<hw>nest egg</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An egg left in the
nest to prevent the hen from forsaking it, and to induce her to lay more
in the same place.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <specif>Hence,</specif> <mark>(figuratively)</mark>,
<def>Money set aside in a special fund to be used for special occasions,
or more commonly, for retirement; <as>as, she set aside a large hunk of
her salary every month and had a considerable <ex>nest egg</ex> for her
retirement</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nestful</ent>⟦br⟧
